# VP / Chief Consulting Officer

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 1 :

- Lead the global consulting organization, reporting directly to the CEO.
- Define the 3-5 year strategic roadmap for the consulting business unit.
- Drive inorganic growth strategies, including identifying and integrating M&A targets.
- Represent the firm to investors and the board of directors.

Skills:
Global strategy definition, M&A integration, Board representation, Investor relations, Strategic roadmap design.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 2 :

- Take full P&L responsibility for the consulting division ($500M+ portfolio).
- Optimize margins through rigorous cost control and delivery model transformation.
- Drive the shift from time-and-materials to outcome-based pricing models.
- Approve large-scale commercial bids and risk frameworks.

Skills:
P&L management, Margin optimization, Commercial strategy, Outcome-based pricing, Risk framework approval.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 3 :

- Architect the firm's global go-to-market (GTM) strategy for consulting services.
- Align consulting sales motions with the broader technology and product sales organizations.
- Build strategic alliances with hyperscalers (AWS, Google, Microsoft) at an executive level.
- Speak at Davos, NRF, or similar global forums to elevate brand prestige.

Skills:
Global GTM strategy, Strategic alliance building, Brand elevation, Sales alignment, Executive thought leadership.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 4 :

- Oversee the delivery excellence function for all consulting engagements globally.
- Standardize methodologies and toolkits across diverse geographies and verticals.
- Manage the "Office of the CCO" to track operational KPIs (utilization, attrition, CSAT).
- Resolve critical escalations involved in multi-million dollar litigious disputes.

Skills:
Delivery excellence, Methodology standardization, Operational KPI tracking, Crisis management, Dispute resolution.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 5 :

- Drive the talent strategy for the consulting workforce (5000+ consultants).
- Redesign the partner compensation and promotion framework.
- Champion diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) initiatives at the leadership level.
- Build a world-class "Consulting Academy" for continuous learning.

Skills:
Talent strategy, Compensation framework design, DEI leadership, Learning academy design, Workforce planning.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 6 :

- Lead the innovation agenda, establishing new practice areas (e.g., Generative AI, Sustainability).
- Manage the R&D budget for developing proprietary IP and assets.
- Foster a culture of entrepreneurship and intrapreneurship among partners.
- Decide on "build vs. buy" for new service lines.

Skills:
Innovation leadership, IP development strategy, R&D budget management, Service line incubation, Entrepreneurship fostering.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 7 :

- Act as the executive sponsor for the firm's top 10 strategic accounts.
- Facilitate CEO-to-CEO dialogues with key clients.
- Drive net revenue retention (NRR) and account expansion strategies.
- Mentor Client Partners on navigating complex C-suite political landscapes.

Skills:
Executive sponsorship, Strategic account management, C-suite relationship building, Net revenue retention, Client partner mentorship.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 8 :

- Consolidate fragmented regional consulting units into a unified global entity.
- Harmonize titles, grades, and career paths across acquired companies.
- Implement a global resource management system to optimize bench utilization.
- Drive cross-border collaboration and "one firm" culture.

Skills:
Organizational restructuring, Post-merger integration, Resource management strategy, Cultural harmonization, Global operations.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 9 :

- Lead the industry vertical strategy (Financial Services, Retail, Healthcare, etc.).
- Appoint and manage Global Sector Heads.
- Define the industry-specific value propositions and solutions.
- Allocate investment funds to high-growth sectors.

Skills:
Vertical strategy leadership, Portfolio management, Investment allocation, Solution value proposition, Sector leadership.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 10 :

- Establish and chair the Consulting Risk Committee.
- Define the firm's risk appetite for complex transformation projects.
- Ensure compliance with global regulations (GDPR, Sovereign Cloud, etc.).
- Oversee the quality assurance (QA) function for high-risk engagements.

Skills:
Risk governance, Compliance oversight, Quality assurance leadership, Risk appetite definition, Regulatory adherence.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 11 :

- Lead the digital transformation of the consulting business itself.
- Implement AI-driven tools to enhance consultant productivity.
- Digitize the knowledge management and IP repository.
- Launch digital-first consulting products (Consulting-as-a-Service).

Skills:
Internal digital transformation, Knowledge management strategy, Productization of services, AI adoption, Operational efficiency.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 12 :

- Develop the firm's sustainability and ESG strategy, both internal and client-facing.
- Position the firm as a leader in the Net Zero transition economy.
- Build partnerships with green tech organizations and NGOs.
- Publish the annual sustainability report for the consulting division.

Skills:
ESG strategy, Sustainability leadership, Partnership building, Brand positioning, Corporate reporting.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 13 :

- Manage the interface between the Consulting and Technology/Outsourcing divisions.
- Design integrated "design-build-run" deals to capture downstream revenue.
- Resolve channel conflicts between consulting and sales teams.
- Create unified incentive structures for cross-functional collaboration.

Skills:
Cross-divisional collaboration, Integrated deal structuring, Conflict resolution, Incentive design, Synergy realization.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 14 :

- Lead the strategy for the Private Equity (PE) channel.
- Build relationships with Operating Partners at top-tier PE firms.
- Develop specialized offerings for pre-deal diligence and post-deal value creation.
- Drive rapid-response capabilities for M&A timelines.

Skills:
Private equity strategy, Diligence advisory, Value creation planning, Channel management, Speed-to-value execution.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 15 :

- Architect the "Future of Work" proposition for clients and internal teams.
- Redefine the hybrid working model for consultants.
- Advise Fortune 100 CHROs on workforce transformation.
- Lead the "People & Change" global practice.

Skills:
Future of work strategy, Workforce transformation, Hybrid model design, CHRO advisory, Change management leadership.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 16 :

- Drive the brand marketing strategy for the consulting division.
- Collaborate with the CMO to define the "Voice of the Firm."
- Oversee the production of flagship thought leadership (e.g., Annual Trends Report).
- Manage the analyst relations strategy (Gartner, Forrester rankings).

Skills:
Brand strategy, Thought leadership direction, Analyst relations, Marketing collaboration, Market positioning.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 17 :

- Lead the turnaround of underperforming practice areas or regions.
- Conduct root cause analysis of margin leakage.
- Execute restructuring plans, including headcount rationalization if necessary.
- Restore profitability and morale in distressed units.

Skills:
Turnaround management, Restructuring, Profitability restoration, Root cause analysis, Change leadership.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 18 :

- Establish a Global Capability Center (GCC) / Offshore delivery model for consulting.
- Scale the "Right-shoring" mix to improve margins.
- Ensure seamless integration between onshore strategy and offshore execution teams.
- Maintain quality standards across distributed delivery centers.

Skills:
Offshore strategy, Global delivery model, Right-shoring, Quality control, Cost optimization.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 19 :

- Serve as the Chief Strategy Officer for the clients' most complex problems.
- Lead "Blue Sky" strategy workshops for client Boards.
- Define new business models and revenue streams for disrupted industries.
- Challenge conventional thinking and drive disruptive innovation.

Skills:
Blue ocean strategy, Business model innovation, Disruption advisory, Board-level facilitation, Strategic foresight.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 20 :

- Manage the firm's ecosystem of boutique consulting partners.
- identifying niche firms for acquisition or strategic partnership.
- Integrate boutique capabilities into large-scale transformation deals.
- Manage the "Partner Network" program.

Skills:
Ecosystem management, Partnership strategy, Acquisition identification, Capability integration, Vendor management.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 21 :

- Lead the public sector strategy at a national/federal level.
- Engage with government ministers and policy makers.
- Oversee the sovereign cloud and national digital identity practices.
- Navigate complex procurement frameworks and political sensitivities.

Skills:
Government relations, Policy advisory, Sovereign capability building, Public sector strategy, Political acumen.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 22 :

- Drive the "Customer Success" philosophy across the consulting lifecycle.
- Implement NPS (Net Promoter Score) systems for client feedback.
- Link partner compensation to client success metrics.
- Create a "Client for Life" culture.

Skills:
Customer success strategy, NPS implementation, Incentive alignment, Culture building, Client loyalty.

